<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="386" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/697:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic"><persName type="from">King Tafari
                                    Makonnen</persName> of Ethiopia to President <persName type="to">Hoover</persName></hi><note n="11" xml:id="d386fn11">Received
                                in the Department of State on December 17, from the White
                                House.</note></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Addis
                                        Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-14">December 14, 1929</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>We concur in and adhere to the message which you have addressed to the
                            Russian and Chinese Governments asking them to use the provisions of the
                            Kellogg Peace Pact for the solution and settlement of their present
                            difficulties. We are willing that you communicate our message to the
                            Russian and Chinese Government[s].</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">King Tafari
                            Makonnen</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>